The paper deals with video object segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves human input through a web game, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of a game to collect human inputs also suggests a possible connection to computer graphics (cs.GR). The method involves optimization of an energy function, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
